description.narrative: By 2020, the access and data management on child survival services are improved., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Health Systems Strengthening, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, disadvantaged girls and boys aged 0-6 years and their families will make progress in realization of their rights to quality and inclusive health care, nutrition and early learning.

description.narrative: UNICEF continued its intensive support to the Ministry of Health in addressing the COVID-19 pandemic, strengthening health system capacities and COVID-19 vaccine roll-out. During the COVID-19 pandemic, UNICEF also provided support to MOH to ensure continuity of child and adolescent health services and their accessibility and availability. In collaboration with regional health authorities, health and nutrition needs of children and women in refugee-like situation were assessed and multi-component support was provided to address them in a sustainable manner. In parallel, regular programme actions on improvement of paediatric care quality at primary healthcare level were implemented effectively. | Status:Met | As-of Date:24/01/2022
